Package emissary.output.roller.journal

Class Journal

  • java.lang.Object
    • emissary.output.roller.journal.Journal
  • public final class Journal
extends Object
    Tracks written progress of a corresponding file. Some formats within the framework don't lend themselves to knowing length of output prior to writing as in many journaled formats. Our model allows us to track successful or complete writes to an output file using JournalEntry objects and is simplified further by using a JournaledChannel.
    See Also:
    JournalReader, JournalWriter

        @Nullable
public JournalEntry getLastEntry()
        Last JournalEntry in the file, which generally represents that last successful written offset in the associated content file.
        Returns:
        Last entry that should correlate to the last good position in a file or null if no entries are present.

      • getLastValidEntry

        @Nullable
public JournalEntry getLastValidEntry​(long channelSize)
        This method retrieves the last valid JournalEntry based on the length or position within the content file. It is possible, on some architectures, that upon a crash data may not have flushed to disk. In this case, we need to query the Journal to find the last good position based on the length of the file.
        Parameters:
        channelSize - The maximum position, generally the file size, to search for
        Returns:
        JournalEntry containing the last good offset less than or equal to channelSize
